  <brief_title>GALLEX 4 - Long-Term Extension Study to Evaluate Tesaglitazar Therapy in Patients With Type 2 Diabetes</brief_title>
  <official_title>A Parallel-Group, Multi-Centre, Active-Controlled (Glibenclamide) Long-Term Extension Study to Evaluate the Safety and Tolerability of Oral Tesaglitazar Therapy in Patients With Type 2 Diabetes</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>AstraZeneca</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>AstraZeneca</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This is a parallel-group, multi-center, long-term extension study from the GALLANT 4 study to
      monitor the safety and tolerability of oral tesaglitazar compared with glibenclamide in
      patients with type 2 diabetes for up to 100 weeks of treatment. The total duration, including
      treatment and follow-up, is 103 weeks.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
